 There are many ways to help you cope with your feelings of depression. It is important that you try some combination of these strategies until you find one or more effective for yourself:

    - Exercise regularly and eat a balanced diet; 

    - Practice relaxation techniques such as deep breathing, yoga, meditation etc.;  

    - Seek social support from family members, friends, and others who understand what it feels like to be in this situation; 

    - Engage in hobbies/activities which give you pleasure, meaningfulness, and satisfaction (such as writing, reading, drawing);  

    - Learn new skills or pursue further education to build self-confidence and reduce negative thoughts about oneself;  

    - Participate in group therapy sessions if possible. These can provide an opportunity to learn coping mechanisms and share experiences with people facing similar challenges; 

    - Consult a medical professional for prescription medications when necessary;  

    - Avoid using drugs or alcohol to numb out painful emotions as they will only make things worse over time.

In addition to taking care of physical health, it’s also crucial to take good care of mental wellbeing. Keep track of mood changes on regular basis and keep seeking for any symptoms associated with other diseases like anxiety disorders or bipolar disorder.</s>

